# Managing Software

## Package Management - APT

In debian distributions and most others, software packages are managed with Advanced Packaging Tool (apt). Which maintains a repository of the packages locally.

### Search (Local Repository)

Check if a software package is available.

```zsh
apt-cache search package-name
```

### Add/Download (Package)

```zsh
apt-get install package-name
```

### Remove (Excludes Configurations)

```zsh
apt-get remove package-name
```

### Remove (Includes Configurations)

```zsh
apt-get purge package-name
```

### Update (Local Repository)

```zsh
apt-get update
```

### Update (Package)

```zsh
apt-get upgrade
```

### Add (Repository)

```zsh
# Append sources.List
cat /etc/apt/sources.list
# Contains references to the repositories applicable

echo "deb http://ppa.launchpad.net/webupd8team/java/ubuntu trusty main" >> /etc/apt/sources.list
echo "debÂ­src http://ppa.launchpad.net/webupd8team/java/ubuntu precise main" >> /etc/apt/sources.list
```

## Package Management - GIT

### Add/Download

```zsh
git clone https://github.com/username/repository-name
```
